UADataType.Description: This structure contains the Calibration information. It is used as an input argument in SetCalibration method. Note: The input data sent in SetCalibration shall be updated in the respective parameters of the asset under Maintenance/Calibration.

Field.Name: LastCalibration
Field.Description: It is the date when the last calibration took place. Note: It can have the initial operation date for a new asset if it is not available.

Field.Name: CalibrationPlace
Field.Description: It is the location where the last calibration took place.

Field.Name: NextCalibration
Field.Description: It is the date of the next planned calibration.

Field.Name: CalibrationValue
Field.Description: It is the actual measured value of the calibration.

Field.Name: SensorScale
Field.Description: It is the nominal scale of the sensor. It corresponds also with the measurement range of the sensor.

Field.Name: CertificateUri
Field.Description: It contains the URI of a certificate of the calibration target in case the calibration target is certified and the information available. Otherwise, the Variable should be omitted. The String shall be a URI as defined by RFC 3986. Example: MCE test document.

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: It defines the engineering unit of the value.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the design value for a given physical quantity. It is used in JointDesignDataType.

Field.Name: PhysicalQuantity
Field.Description: It is the physical quantity of the value. Example: Force, Angle, etc.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the given value.

Field.Name: DesignValue
Field.Description: It is the design value. The data type can be any simple data type such as Integer, String, Double, DateTime, etc. If the value is corresponding to the physical quantity, then the data type should be Double.

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: It is the engineering unit of the value.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the identification data for a given entity in the system.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the entity identifier. Examples: VIN, Program Id, etc. Note: Application can send custom names which could be a combination of different terms in the system.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is the description of the entity. Any additional information for the entity can be sent using this property. Examples: Name of the program in the given system.

Field.Name: EntityId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the given entity. Examples: JoiningProcessId, JointId, etc.

Field.Name: EntityOriginId
Field.Description: It is the origin identifier of the given entity. It is provided only when it is applicable and available for a given entity. Examples: JoiningProcessOriginId, JointOriginId, etc.

Field.Name: IsExternal
Field.Description: It indicates if the EntityId is provided by the external system or not. Example: VIN is provided by an external system.

Field.Name: EntityType
Field.Description: It provides the type of the Entity. It has the following pre-defined values which shall be used for each instance of this type. Important Note: EntityType >=0 is defined as part of this specification. For application specific extensions, EntityType < 0 can be used.

UADataType.Description: It is used report errors occurred in the system which are outside the boundaries of the given program.

Field.Name: ErrorType
Field.Description: It is the classification of type of errors due to external factors. Examples: Tool Trigger Lost is Operator error. Temperature overheat is hardware error, etc.

Field.Name: ErrorId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the error in the system. This will be useful if system wants to provide an identifier where user can query the system and get more information for troubleshooting. It can also point to the respective EventId reported if available.

Field.Name: LegacyError
Field.Description: It is the application or system specific error code.

Field.Name: ErrorMessage
Field.Description: It is user readable text message to describe the error.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the base container for any joining process in a joining system. Note: This specification defines the meta data of a JoiningProcess, and the actual content of the Joining Process is application specific.

Field.Name: JoiningProcessMetaData
Field.Description: It is the meta data of the joining process.

Field.Name: JoiningProcessContent
Field.Description: It is the actual content of the joining process which is defined by JoiningProcessMetaData.Classification property. Examples: Joining Program, Joining Job, etc. Note: The content is application-specific and is not defined in this version of the specification.

UADataType.Description: This structure contains the identification information of a Joining Process. It is used in set of methods defined in JoiningProcessManagementType.

Field.Name: JoiningProcessId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the joining process.

Field.Name: JoiningProcessOriginId
Field.Description:
It is an identifier to track the changes made to the original instance in the system.
Example: It can point to the identifier of the object when it was created for the first time. It should be an existing ID in the system if it is available else it can be NULL if it is not tracked in the system.

Field.Name: SelectionName
Field.Description: It is the configured selection name of the joining process in the system.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the meta data which describes the joining process.

Field.Name: JoiningProcessId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the joining process.

Field.Name: JoiningProcessOriginId
Field.Description: It is an identifier to track the changes made to the original instance in the system. Example: It can point to the identifier of the object when it was created for the first time. It should be an existing ID in the system if it is available else it can be NULL if it is not tracked in a joining system.

Field.Name: CreationTime
Field.Description: It is the time when the joining process was created.

Field.Name: LastUpdatedTime
Field.Description: It is the time when the joining process was updated last time. If it is not available, it can be same as CreationTime.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the joining process.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is the description of the joining process.

Field.Name: JoiningTechnology
Field.Description: It is a human readable text to identify the joining technology.

Field.Name: Classification
Field.Description: It is the classification of the joining process.

UADataType.Description: It is used report data associated with Joining Result and the corresponding measurement values.

Field.Name: FailureReason
Field.Description: It provides the primary reason for failure. If a violation is handled by a rework step resulting in a successful operation, then it is not reported as failure.

Field.Name: OverallResultValues
Field.Description:
It is an array of overall result values which contains the measurement values of different quantities like torque, angle, time, etc. based on the program.
Note: If the operation is terminated in the first step and no values are available to report, then this list may be empty.

Field.Name: StepResults
Field.Description: It is an array of step results corresponding to each step in the program. This parameter is used if the system provides one or more step results.

Field.Name: Errors
Field.Description: It is an array of external errors which captures the failures outside the boundary of the program are captured as part of the Errors. It is up to the application to fill in the critical/primary error in the Errors list as top entry.

Field.Name: FailingStepResultId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the step result which is the primary cause of failure.

Field.Name: Trace
Field.Description: It is a structure to include the Joining Trace content. This can be NULL or empty and it is up to the application to send this as part of the Joining Result.

UADataType.Description: This structure is a subtype of 5:ResultMetaDataType. It is used to define additional meta data of a Result in a joining system.

Field.Name: JoiningTechnology
Field.Description: It is a human readable text to identify the joining technology.

Field.Name: SequenceNumber
Field.Description: It is the cyclic counter which is incremented for each result generated.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the user-friendly name of the result. Examples: Job Result, Batch Result, etc.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is the additional information associated with the result. It can contain information on the 5:ResultConent.

Field.Name: Classification
Field.Description: It provides information on the classification of the result in the joining system.

Field.Name: OperationMode
Field.Description: It provides information on how the joining process was selected.

Field.Name: AssemblyType
Field.Description: It provides the type of joining operation.

Field.Name: AssociatedEntities
Field.Description: It is a list of identifiers associated to the given result. Examples: ProductId, VIN, SocketId, JointId, JoiningProcessId, etc.

Field.Name: ResultCounters
Field.Description: It is a list of counters associated to the given result. Examples: Batch Counter, Retry Counter, Channel Counter, etc.

Field.Name: InterventionType
Field.Description: It provides information on type of intervention which has occurred during the joining operation.

Field.Name: IsGeneratedOffline
Field.Description: It indicates that the result is generated when the asset was offline. The default value is false. Note: The definition of offline status is application specific. Example: Wireless tool performing joining in radio shadow.

UADataType.Description: This structure is the base container for any joint component such as Bolt, Rivet, Gasket, Glue string, etc. Note: The concrete definition of joint component is not defined in this version of the specification.

Field.Name: JointComponentId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the joint component. Examples: BoltId, RivetId, GasketId, etc.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the joint component.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is the description of the joint component.

Field.Name: Manufacturer
Field.Description: It is the manufacturer of the joint component.

Field.Name: ManufacturerUri
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the manufacturer.

Field.Name: JointComponentContent
Field.Description: It is the content of the joint component. Examples: Bolt, Rivet, Gasket, etc.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the joint information. Joint is the physical outcome of the joining operation which determines the properties of the point where multiple parts are assembled.

Field.Name: JointId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the joint.

Field.Name: JointOriginId
Field.Description:
It is an identifier to track the changes made to the original instance in the system.
Example: It can point to the identifier of the object when it was created for the first time. It should be an existing ID in the system if it is available else it can be NULL if it is not tracked in a joining system.

Field.Name: JointDesignId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the associated joint design.

Field.Name: CreationTime
Field.Description: It is the time when the joint was created.

Field.Name: LastUpdatedTime
Field.Description: It is the time when the joint was updated last time. If it is not available, it can be same as CreationTime.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the joint.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is the description of the joint.

Field.Name: Classification
Field.Description: It is the classification of the joint.

Field.Name: ClassificationDetails
Field.Description:
It is the details of the classification. It can also be used to provide any other type of classification.
Examples: Safety Critical, etc.

Field.Name: JointStatus
Field.Description: It is the status of the joint. Examples: Ok, InUse, NotInUse, NotYetDone, etc.

Field.Name: AssociatedEntities
Field.Description: It is the list of entities associated to the joint. Examples: JoiningProcessId, JobId, QualityProcessId, SimulationProcessId, etc.

Field.Name: JoiningTechnology
Field.Description: It is a human readable text to identify the joining technology.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the design information of a given joint.

Field.Name: JointDesignId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the joint design.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the joint design.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is the description of the joint design.

Field.Name: JointDesignContent
Field.Description: It is the list of design values.

Field.Name: JointComponentIdList
Field.Description: It is the list of joint components associated to the joint design. Examples: BoltId, RivetId, GasketId, etc.

UADataType.Description: This structure provides the given value and corresponding limits for a given physical quantity (if applicable).

Field.Name: PhysicalQuantity
Field.Description: It is the physical quantity of the value. Example: Torque, Angle, etc. Note: It may not be applicable for few reported values such as Software Version, etc.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the given value.

Field.Name: CurrentValue
Field.Description: It is the current value. The data type can be any simple data type such as Integer, String, Double, DateTime, etc. If the value is corresponding to the physical quantity, then the recommended data type is Double.

Field.Name: PreviousValue
Field.Description: It is the previous value (if available). The data type can be any simple data type such as Integer, String, Double, DateTime, etc. If the value is corresponding to the physical quantity, then the data type should be Double.

Field.Name: LowLimit
Field.Description: It is the low limit of the given value. It is not applicable for values which does not have PhysicalQuantity.

Field.Name: HighLimit
Field.Description: It is the high limit of the given value. It is not applicable for values which does not have PhysicalQuantity.

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: It defines the engineering unit of the value. It is not applicable for values which does not have PhysicalQuantity.

UADataType.Description: This structure is used to provide various types of counters associated to a Result. These counters are related to a joining process with sub-processes.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the name of the counter.

Field.Name: CounterValue
Field.Description: It is the value of the counter.

Field.Name: CounterType
Field.Description: It is the type of the Counter.

UADataType.Description: It is used to report measurement values of the joining operation. Those are meant to characterize the quality of the process. It is used in JoiningResultDataType and StepResultDataType.

Field.Name: MeasuredValue
Field.Description: It is the measured value of the given result. The value corresponds to the PhysicalQuantity attribute of JoiningDataVariableType.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is a user readable name of the given measurement value.

Field.Name: ResultEvaluation
Field.Description: It indicates whether the measured value is as per the configured limits and corresponds to a successful result or not.

Field.Name: ValueId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the given value if it is available in the system.

Field.Name: ValueTag
Field.Description: It is an associated tag to the given measurement value to classify it based on the joining domain. Examples: FINAL, YIELD, SNUG, etc.

Field.Name: TracePointIndex
Field.Description: It is the index to the trace sample array from which corresponds to this specific result.

Field.Name: TracePointTimeOffset
Field.Description: It is the time offset to point out the absolute time point in the array of trace samples. This may or may not match with an element in the TraceContent array. If it is not available in the TraceContent array, the value can be visualized in the trace graph via interpolation or some other plotting mechanisms.

Field.Name: ParameterIdList
Field.Description: It is an array of parameter identifiers configured in the Program which is being monitored or sampled. Note: In most common cases, it can be a single identifier.

Field.Name: ViolationType
Field.Description: Indicates whether the measured value is above or below the configured limit. It is only relevant if program or step configuration is violated.

Field.Name: ViolationConsequence
Field.Description: It provides information on the consequence occurred due to the violation of the configurable limits. Examples: Step Transition, Abort Joining Operation. Is the consequence repairable or not, etc.

Field.Name: SensorId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the sensor which has reported the value.

Field.Name: LowLimit
Field.Description: It provides the lower limit of the measured value as per the program.

Field.Name: HighLimit
Field.Description: It provides the upper limit of the measured value as per the program.

Field.Name: TargetValue
Field.Description: It provides the target value of the specific measurement in the program step.

Field.Name: ResultStep
Field.Description: It provides the step number or name of the program step which has generated the result. Note: This is not applicable for StepResultValues in StepResultDataType. This is added for OverallResultValues in JoiningResultDataType to get the information of the step which has reported the specific value.

Field.Name: PhysicalQuantity
Field.Description: It is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given value(s).

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: It is the engineering unit of the value.

UADataType.Description: This structure contains the signal information which is used in SetIOSignals and GetIOSignals methods.

Field.Name: SignalId
Field.Description: It is the identifier of the signal.

Field.Name: SignalValue
Field.Description: It is the value of the signal.

Field.Name: SignalDescription
Field.Description: It is the description of the signal.

Field.Name: SignalType
Field.Description: It is the type of the signal.

UADataType.Description: It is used report measurement values corresponding to a given step in the program. It is used in JoiningResultDataType.

Field.Name: StepResultId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the step result.

Field.Name: ProgramStepId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the Program Step.

Field.Name: ProgramStep
Field.Description: It is the step number or name of the program step. Sometimes the step id is like 2A, 3B based on number of branches. Hence a string place holder is needed instead of number.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the user-friendly name of the given step. This can be the name of the step in the configuration for ease of use and troubleshooting.

Field.Name: ResultEvaluation
Field.Description: It indicates if the StepResult is successful or not.

Field.Name: StartTimeOffset
Field.Description: It is the offset to the ProcessingTimes.StartTime in Result, this value can be used to order the steps in execution order if same step is run multiple times.

Field.Name: StepTraceId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the StepTrace associated to the StepResult.

Field.Name: StepResultValues
Field.Description: It is the set of values which needs to be measured as per the program step.

UADataType.Description: It is to describe of the trace for a given program step. It is used in JoiningTraceDataType.

Field.Name: StepTraceId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the step trace.

Field.Name: StepResultId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated step result.

Field.Name: NumberOfTracePoints
Field.Description: It is the total number of trace points to be sent for each quantity.

Field.Name: SamplingInterval
Field.Description: It is the time between each sample in the given Trace array. This is required if applications want to reduce the amount of data by omitting the StepTraceContent array which represents TIME.

Field.Name: StartTimeOffset
Field.Description: It is the offset to the ProcessingTimes.StartTime in the Result instance. This value can be used to order the steps in execution order if same step is run multiple times.

Field.Name: StepTraceContent
Field.Description: It is an array of trace data which contains the samples of different quantities like torque, angle, time, etc. The array size of TraceContent array should be same for each quantity and that is determined by the NumberOfTracePoints value.

UADataType.Description: It is to describe of the trace samples for a given program step. It is used in StepTraceDataType.

Field.Name: Values
Field.Description: It is an array of trace samples. The values correspond to the PhysicalQuantity attribute.

Field.Name: SensorId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the sensor which has reported the values. This will be useful for identifying the sensor when the same set of samples are reported by multiple sensors.

Field.Name: Name
Field.Description: It is the user-friendly name for the given trace.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: It is an additional text to describe the trace samples.

Field.Name: PhysicalQuantity
Field.Description: It is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given value(s).

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: It is the engineering unit of the values.

UADataType.Description: It is a base type to encapsulate common data for a Trace.

Field.Name: TraceId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the Trace.

Field.Name: ResultId
Field.Description: It is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated result. This is useful to link Result and Trace instances when the Result and Trace are sent separately.

UADataType.Description: This structure is to describe the content of traces for all the steps in the given program. It is used in JoiningResultDataType.

Field.Name: StepTraces
Field.Description: It is an array of StepTraceDataType which provides trace content for each step in the given result.

UAVariableType.Description: The JoiningDataVariableType is a subtype of the BaseDataVariableType. It is to describe common sematic required for variables in the system. In this version of the specification, it provides information about physical quantity and Engineering Units.

UAVariable.Description: The optional 0:EngineeringUnits defines the engineering unit of the values.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given value(s).

UAVariableType.Description: The JoiningSystemEventContentType is a subtype of 0:BaseVariableType. It is used JoiningSystemEventType and JoiningSystemConditionType.

UAVariable.Description: AssociatedEntities is a list of identifiers of various entities/objects available in the given system. Example: An event maybe associated to Asset, Result, Joint, Error, etc.
EventCode is a system specific event code associated to the given event.
EventText is a human readable text related to the context of the event.
JoiningTechnology is a human readable text to identify the joining technology which has triggered the event. Examples: Tightening, Gluing, Riveting, Flow Drill Fastening, etc.

ReportedValues is a list of values associated with the given event payload. Example: If it is an over temperature event, then the ReportedValue can be the measured value along with the corresponding limits.

UAVariableType.Description: The JoiningSystemResultType is a subtype of 0:BaseVariableType. It is used to expose the information of the 5:ResultDataType in individual sub-variables.

UAObjectType.Description: Indicates that an entity is accepted.
Indicates that an entity is added.
Indicates that the asset is connected.
Indicates that the asset is disabled.
Indicates that the asset is disconnected.
Indicates that the asset is enabled.
Indicates a change in the asset location.
Indicates a change in the certificate.
Indicates a change in the configuration.
Indicates a failure in the data validation.
Indicates an error in the system.
Indicates that an entity is expired.
Indicates a change in the hardware entity.
Indicates that an entity is incompatible.
Indicates a failure in the input validation.
Indicates that an entity is invalid.
Indicates that a joining system user has logged-in.
Indicates that a joining system user logged-out.
Indicates a change in the joint location.
Indicates a change in the license.
Indicates the change of the entity location is in the range.
Indicates the change in the entity location is out of range.
Indicates that an entity is missing.
Indicates that an entity is rejected.
Indicates that an entity is rejected.
Indicates that an entity is removed.
Indicates a change in the software entity.
Indicates that a threshold is violated.
Indicates that a violated threshold is resolved.
Indicates that an entity is updated.

The JoiningSystemConditionType is used to send any type of events with acknowledgement mechanism from a joining system. Note: The type of event is determined by the usage of respective Condition Class(es) and Condition Subclass(es) properties defined in 0:ConditionType.

UAVariable.Description: JoiningSystemEventContent is the common payload of the event from a joining system.
AssociatedEntities is a list of identifiers of various entities/objects available in the given system. Example: An event maybe associated to Asset, Result, Joint, Error, etc.
EventCode is a system specific event code associated to the given event.
EventText is a human readable text related to the context of the event.
JoiningTechnology is a human readable text to identify the joining technology which has triggered the event. Examples: Tightening, Gluing, Riveting, Flow Drill Fastening, etc.

ReportedValues is a list of values associated with the given event payload. Example: If it is an over temperature event, then the ReportedValue can be the measured value along with the corresponding limits.

UAObjectType.Description: The JoiningSystemEventType is used to send any type of events from a joining system. Note: The type of event is determined by the usage of respective Condition Class(es) and Condition Subclass(es) properties defined in 0:BaseEventType.

UAVariable.Description: JoiningSystemEventContent is the common payload of the event from a joining system.
AssociatedEntities is a list of identifiers of various entities/objects available in the given system. Example: An event maybe associated to Asset, Result, Joint, Error, etc.
EventCode is a system specific event code associated to the given event.
EventText is a human readable text related to the context of the event.
JoiningTechnology is a human readable text to identify the joining technology which has triggered the event. Examples: Tightening, Gluing, Riveting, Flow Drill Fastening, etc.

ReportedValues is a list of values associated with the given event payload. Example: If it is an over temperature event, then the ReportedValue can be the measured value along with the corresponding limits.

UAObjectType.Description: This EventType provides information of a complete or partial result from a joining system.

UAVariable.Description: CreationTime indicates the time when the result was created. Creation time on the measurement system (not the receive time of the server). It is recommended to always provide the creationTime.

Value.uax:String: External ID of the Configuration in use while the result was produced. It is managed by the Environment. This specification does not define how the externalConfigurationId is transmitted to the system. Typically, it is provided by the client.

UAVariable.Description: External ID of the recipe in use which produced the result. The External ID is managed by the environment. This specification does not define how the externalRecipeId is transmitted to the system. Typically, it is provided by the client.

The format in which the measurement results are available (e.g. QDAS, CSV, ) using the ResultTransfer Object. If multiple file formats are provided, the GenerateFileForRead of ResultTransfer should contain corresponding transferOptions, to select the file format. This specification does not define those transferOptions.
Indicates that additional data for this result can be retrieved by temporary file transfer. If not provided, it is assumed that no file is available.
Internal ID of the Configuration in use while the result was produced. This ID is system-wide unique and it is assigned by the system.
Internal ID of the recipe in use which produced the result. This ID is system-wide unique and it is assigned by the system.
Indicates whether the result is the partial result of a total result. When not all samples are finished yet the result is 'partial'. If not provided, it is assumed to be a total result.

Indicates whether the result was created in simulation mode. Simulation mode implies that the result is only generated for testing purposes and not based on real production data. If not provided, it is assumed to not be simulated.
Identifies the job which produced the result. This ID is system-wide unique and it is assigned by the system.

Identifies the part used to produce the result. Although the system-wide unique JobId would be sufficient to identify the job which the result belongs to, this makes for easier filtering without keeping track of JobIds. This specification does not define how the partId is transmitted to the system. Typically, it is provided by the client when starting the job.
Collection of different processing times that were needed to create the result.

Value.uax:String: Identifies the product used to produce the result. This specification does not define how the externalRecipeId is transmitted to the system. Typically, it is provided by the client.

UAVariable.Description: The ResultEvaluation indicates whether the result was in tolerance.
Vendor-specific code describing more details on resultEvaluation.
The optional EvaluationDetails provides high level status information in a user-friendly text. This can be left empty for successful operations.

ResultState provides information about the current state of the process or measurement creating a result. Applications may use negative values for application-specific states. All other values shall only be used as defined in the following: 0 Undefined initial value 1 Completed: Processing was carried out completely 2 Processing: Processing has not been finished yet 3 Aborted: Processing was stopped at some point before completion 4 Failed: Processing failed in some way.
Path to the actual measured result, managed external to the server.

Identifies the step which produced the result. Although the system-wide unique JobId would be sufficient to identify the job which the result belongs to, this makes for easier filtering without keeping track of JobIds. This specification does not define how the stepId is transmitted to the system. Typically, it is provided by the client when starting an execution.

UAObjectType.Description: The IJoiningAdditionalInformationType provides additional parameters for Identification of a given asset.

UAVariable.Description: Description is the system specific description of the asset.
JoiningTechnology is a human readable text to identify the joining technology.
SupplierCode is the SAP or ERP Supplier Code of the asset.

UAObjectType.Description: This is a generic interface common for all assets in a given Joining System. The purpose of this interface is to provide a standard way of identification and common information for all the assets. This interface has a standard MachineryItemIdentificationType add-in which can be assigned with MachineIdentificationType or MachineryComponentIdentificationType for a given asset based on the requirement of the system.

UAObject.Description: The Health Object is an instance of 2:FunctionalGroupType to group health related parameters for all the assets in a Joining System.

UAVariable.Description: DeviceHealth indicates the status as defined by NAMUR Recommendation NE107. Clients can read or monitor this Variable to determine the device condition.
ErrorCode is the system specific code for the error occurred.
ErrorMessage is the user readable text of the error reported by the given asset.
ErrorTimestamp is the timestamp when the error occurred in the given asset.
Temperature is the measured temperature of the asset.

UAObject.Description: The Identification Object, using the standardized name defined in OPC 10000-100, provides identification information about the asset. This is a mandatory place holder and any asset inheriting ITighteningSystemAssetType will replace it with MachineIdentificationType or MachineryComponentIdentificationType.

UAVariable.Description: To be used by end users to store a unique identification in the context of their overall application. Servers shall support at least 40 Unicode characters for the clients writing this value, this means clients can expect to be able to write strings with a length of 40 Unicode characters into that field.

To be used by end users to store a human-readable localized text for the MachineryItem. The minimum number of locales supported for this property shall be two. Servers shall support at least 40 Unicode characters for the clients writing the text part of each locale, this means clients can expect to be able to write texts with a length of 40 Unicode characters into that field.
Description is the system specific description of the asset.
Indicates in which domain or for what purpose the MachineryItem is used.

A string representation of the revision level of the hardware of a MachineryItem. Hardware is physical equipment, as opposed to programs, procedures, rules and associated documentation. Many machines will not provide such information due to the modular and configurable nature of the machine.
The date, when the MachineryItem was switched on the first time after it has left the manufacturer plant.
JoiningTechnology is a human readable text to identify the joining technology.
A human-readable, localized name of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem.
A globally unique identifier of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem.
A human-readable, localized name of the model of the MachineryItem.
The month in which the manufacturing process of the MachineryItem has been completed. It shall be a number between 1 and 12, representing the month from January to December.

UAObject.Description: It provides information about the duration something is turned on and how long it performs an activity.

UAVariable.Description: OperationCycleCounter is counting the times the component switches from not performing an activity to performing an activity. For example, each time a valve starts moving, is counted. This value shall only increase during the lifetime of the component and shall not be reset when the component is restarted.

OperationDuration is the duration the MachineryItem has been powered and performing an activity. This counter is intended for machines and components where a distinction is made between switched on and in operation. For example, a drive might be powered on but not operating. It is not intended for machines or components always performing an activity like sensors always measuring data. This value shall only increase during the lifetime of the MachineryItem and shall not be reset when it is restarted. The OperationDuration is provided as Duration, i.e., in milliseconds or even fractions of a millisecond. However, the Server is not expected to update the value in such a high frequency, but maybe once a minute or once an hour, depending on the application.

PowerOnDuration is the duration the MachineryItem has been powered. The main purpose is to determine the time in which degradation of the MachineryItem occurred. The details, when the time is counted, is implementation-specific. Companion specifications might define specific rules. Typically, when the MachineryItem has supply voltage and the main CPU is running, the time is counted. This may include any kind of sleep mode, but may not include pure Wake on LAN. This value shall only increase during the lifetime of the MachineryItem and shall not be reset when it is restarted. The PowerOnDuration is provided as Duration, i.e., in milliseconds or even fractions of a millisecond. However, the Server is not expected to update the value in such a high frequency, but maybe once a minute or once an hour, depending on the application.
